                <h1>Susan B. Anthony: Champion of Women's Rights</h1>
                <p>Susan B. Anthony was a pioneering advocate for women's rights in the United States. Born in 1820, she played a crucial role in the women's suffrage movement, tirelessly campaigning for women's right to vote. Her efforts laid the groundwork for future reforms, and her legacy continues to inspire generations advocating for equality.</p>
